<p class="p">The impacts of extreme high-temperature events that are avoided by a lower warming level (e.g., 2.0 °C or 1.5 °C) compared with the INDC scenario were investigated using the following equation:
 <disp-formula id="FD2-ijerph-16-02661" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(2)</label>
  <math id="mm9" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">Avoid</mi>
      <mtext class="mtext"> </mtext>
      <mi class="mi">Imapct</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mfrac class="mfrac">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">C</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">I</mi>
         <mi class="mi">N</mi>
         <mi class="mi">D</mi>
         <mi class="mi">C</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <mo class="mo">−</mo>
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">C</mi>
        <mi class="mi">k</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">C</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">I</mi>
         <mi class="mi">N</mi>
         <mi class="mi">D</mi>
         <mi class="mi">C</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
     <mo class="mo">,</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm10" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi class="mi">C</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> represents the changes in extreme high-temperature indices under a specific scenario compared with the present climatology, and the subscript 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm11" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi class="mi">k</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> indicates different scenarios (e.g., 2.0 °C/1.5 °C). Such information is beneficial for future mitigation and adaptation planning.
</p>
